title Domain Model â€“ US 2.2.1 (Create & Update Vessel Types)

class VesselType <<Aggregate Root>> {
  + VesselTypeId : string
  + Name : string
  + Description : string
  + MaxCapacityTEU : int
  + MaxRows : int
  + MaxBays : int
  + MaxTiers : int
  + MaxLength : decimal
  + MaxBeam : decimal
  + MaxDraft : decimal
  --
  + VesselType(name:string, description:string, maxCapacityTEU:int, maxRows:int, maxBays:int, maxTiers:int, maxLength:decimal, maxBeam:decimal, maxDraft:decimal)
  + Update(description:string, maxCapacityTEU:int, maxRows:int, maxBays:int, maxTiers:int, maxLength:decimal, maxBeam:decimal, maxDraft:decimal) : void
}

class Vessel {
  + ImoNumber : string
  + Name : string
  + VesselTypeId : string
  + Length : decimal
  + Beam : decimal
  + Draft : decimal
  + CapacityTEU : int
  --
  Constraints:
  Length <= VesselType.MaxLength
  Beam <= VesselType.MaxBeam
  Draft <= VesselType.MaxDraft
  CapacityTEU <= VesselType.MaxCapacityTEU
}

class Dock {
  + DockCode : string
  + Length : decimal
  + Depth : decimal
  + DockType : enum
  --
  Can accommodate vessels where:
  Vessel.Length <= Dock.Length
  Vessel.Draft <= Dock.Depth
}

note right of VesselType
  **Invariants:**
  - Name must be unique
  - All numeric values must be positive
  - Name cannot be null or empty
  
  **Purpose:**
  Defines maximum operational constraints
  and physical dimensions for vessel classification
end note

note left of Vessel
  Individual vessels reference a VesselType
  and cannot exceed its maximum dimensions.
  This is validated in US 2.2.2.
end note

note right of Dock
  Docks must be able to accommodate
  vessel types based on physical constraints.
  VesselType max dimensions inform dock
  capacity planning.
end note

